<TITLE> 24 suspected militants detained in Chandpur </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chandpur, Dec 14 (bdnews24.com)  Chandpur police Friday arrested 24 suspected militants in Kachua Upazila of the district. Police said all of the youths admitted that they were members of Islamist organisation Hizbut Tauheed. They were picked up from Kachua Bazaar, Fire Service Office area, Khagra village and some other places of the upazila. Police arrested Rasel Bhuiyan, Sajjad Hossain and Aminul Islam of Munshiganj, Rabiul Islam Rabi of Morelganj, Bagerhat; Anisur Rahman Akbar of Babuganj, Barisal; Habibur Rahman of West Hatalia, Patuakhali; Sirajil Islam Mintu of Rupsha, Khulna, and Nasir Uddin Ahmed and Nahid Khan of Kumarkhali, Kushtia in the first phase during their drive. Later in the evening, they arrested 15 more, name of whom could not be known immediately. Kachua police chief Anisul Islam told bdnews24.com they seized flyers calling for Islamic revolution, CDs and some religion-based books from the detainees. Anisul said the young men told police they went to Chandpur from Dhaka to wage a religious campaign. Chandpur police superintendent Obaidur Rahman Khan said the detainees were being interrogated. He said the arrestees confessed that a team of 40 arrived in Kachua. Another team went to Matlab, but they did not know the number. "Our drive is going on. We have already alerted all police stations in Chandpur," he added. bdnews24.comcor
